data.name: picHelpTextExtRules.ToolTip
data.value:
Rule format: extension = the first line character of the text corresponding to this extension (supports the regular expression).
For text type files, the first non blank line will be matched. When matching is successful, the corresponding custom extension is used by default.
For example: cs=^using .*;$ java=^package.*;$ html=(? i)<!DOCTYPE html cpp=^#include.*
